<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3076] Allow to disable automatic shipping of dependency jars for mapreduce jobs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3076</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3001&quot; title=&quot;Ship dependency jars to the cluster for all jobs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3001&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3001&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, TableMapReduceUtil.initTableMap/ReduceJob will automatically upload the HBase jars needed to execute a map reduce job.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my case I am building a job jar using Maven&apos;s assembly plugin, this way all the necessary dependencies are in the job jar. So in such case the default behavior of HBase causes some needless upload work. It also uploads hadoop-core itself which is not necessary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore I propose to add a variant of the initTableMap/ReduceJob methods with an extra boolean argument to disable the automatic adding of dependency jars.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will attach a patch with the proposed change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that everything works as is, this is just an optimization.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
